# Portfolio Status Normalization Handoff

## Decision

After DEX-REQ-11, pause further functional DEX evolution and start:

`PORTFOLIO STATUS NORMALIZATION`

## Trigger

DEX completed the current L4 readiness technical cycle through DEX-REQ-11.

## Target Nuclei

- Academy
- ACS
- Business
- Marketplace
- Mining
- Trading

## Objective

Create or normalize `.instructions/STATUS.md` in each target nucleus and establish comparable maturity evidence across the portfolio.

## Required Deliverables Per Nucleus

- `.instructions/STATUS.md`
- L1-L5 maturity proposal
- current operational status
- blockers
- dependencies
- risks
- latest evidence
- recommended next request
- production/execution policy
- portfolio handoff note where applicable

## DEX Post-REQ-11 Containment

Allowed:

- status updates
- roadmap updates
- local validation evidence
- portfolio handoff
- consumer contract documentation
- minor consistency corrections

Not allowed without explicit executive approval:

- swap execution
- wallet signing
- on-chain transaction submission
- liquidity routing
- treasury integration
- trading automation
- production provider dependency
- executable smart contracts

## Expected Outcome

The Axodus portfolio should have comparable status and maturity evidence across all major nuclei, enabling objective prioritization, blocker handling, maturity promotion, and operational audit.

## Versioning Note

`/opt/Axodus` is a coordination shell and is not a Git repository. This handoff is local/unversioned unless later migrated to a versioned portfolio documentation location.
